@startuml sequence_authorization
skinparam monochrome true
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam SequenceArrowColor #333333
skinparam SequenceLifeLineBorderColor #333333
skinparam SequenceParticipantBorderColor #333333
skinparam SequenceBoxBorderColor #333333
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam NoteBorderColor #333333

title Cleaning Platform — JWT Authorization Flow\n(Decentralized token validation, no IAC round-trip)

actor "Client User" as USER
participant "UI Service\n(:18090)" as UI
participant "IAC Service\n(:18080)" as IAC
participant "JwtTokenProvider\n(IAC)" as JWT_IAC
participant "Property Service\n(:18081)" as PROP
participant "JwtAuthFilter\n(Property)" as PROP_FILTER
participant "JwtTokenProvider\n(Property)" as JWT_PROP
participant "Order Service\n(:18083)" as ORDER
participant "JwtAuthFilter\n(Order)" as ORDER_FILTER
database "Shared JWT_SECRET\n(env var)" as SECRET

note over IAC, SECRET
  All microservices share the SAME JWT_SECRET via environment variable.
  Each service independently validates tokens — zero inter-service calls per request.
end note

== Step 1: Login and obtain JWT ==

USER -> UI: POST /api/v1/auth/login\n{username: "alice", password: "..."}
UI -> IAC: forward to IAC Service
IAC -> IAC: AuthService.login()
IAC -> IAC: validate credentials against DB
IAC -> JWT_IAC: generateAccessToken(username, roles, userId)
JWT_IAC -> SECRET: sign with HS256 + JWT_SECRET
SECRET --> JWT_IAC: signed token
JWT_IAC --> IAC: accessToken (15 min TTL)\n+ refreshToken (7 days)
IAC --> UI: {accessToken, refreshToken, userId, roles}
UI --> USER: tokens stored in session cookie

note right of JWT_IAC
  JWT Claims:
  - sub: "alice"
  - roles: ["ROLE_USER", "ROLE_CLIENT"]
  - userId: "550e8400-..."
  - iat, exp
end note

== Step 2: Accessing Property Service (ROLE_CLIENT required) ==

USER -> UI: GET /properties (view my properties)
UI -> PROP: GET /api/v1/properties\nAuthorization: Bearer <accessToken>

PROP -> PROP_FILTER: doFilterInternal(request)
PROP_FILTER -> PROP_FILTER: extract token from header
PROP_FILTER -> JWT_PROP: isTokenValid(token)
JWT_PROP -> SECRET: verify signature with shared JWT_SECRET
SECRET --> JWT_PROP: signature OK
JWT_PROP -> JWT_PROP: check exp claim (not expired)
JWT_PROP --> PROP_FILTER: true

PROP_FILTER -> JWT_PROP: extractUsername(token)
JWT_PROP --> PROP_FILTER: "alice"
PROP_FILTER -> PROP_FILTER: loadUserByUsername("alice")\n[local UserDetails from JWT claims]
PROP_FILTER -> PROP_FILTER: setAuthentication()\n(principal + authorities from JWT)

note right of PROP_FILTER
  Property Service does NOT call IAC.
  Roles are decoded from JWT claims.
  UserDetails built in-memory from token.
end note

PROP_FILTER --> PROP: authenticated context set

PROP -> PROP: @PreAuthorize("hasRole('CLIENT')")
PROP -> PROP: check SecurityContext authorities
alt Missing ROLE_CLIENT
    PROP --> USER: 403 Forbidden
else Has ROLE_CLIENT
    PROP -> PROP: propertyService.findByClientId(userId)
    PROP --> UI: 200 OK [PropertyList]
    UI --> USER: render properties page
end

== Step 3: Creating Order (ROLE_CLIENT, property validation) ==

USER -> UI: POST /orders (create cleaning order)
UI -> ORDER: POST /api/v1/orders\nAuthorization: Bearer <accessToken>

ORDER -> ORDER_FILTER: doFilterInternal(request)
ORDER_FILTER -> JWT_PROP: validate token (same logic)
JWT_PROP --> ORDER_FILTER: valid, username="alice"
ORDER_FILTER -> ORDER_FILTER: setAuthentication()

ORDER -> ORDER: @PreAuthorize("hasRole('CLIENT')")
ORDER -> ORDER: extract userId from SecurityContext\n(UUID from JWT claim)

ORDER -> PROP: HTTP GET /api/v1/properties/{propId}/validate\nAuthorization: Bearer <accessToken> (service-to-service)

note right of ORDER
  Order Service passes the SAME user JWT
  to Property Service for ownership validation.
  Property Service validates token independently.
end note

PROP -> PROP_FILTER: validate token
PROP_FILTER --> PROP: authenticated
PROP -> PROP: check property owner == userId
alt Ownership mismatch
    PROP --> ORDER: 403 Forbidden
    ORDER --> USER: 403 Property not owned by user
else Owner matches
    PROP --> ORDER: 200 OK {valid: true, property details}
    ORDER -> ORDER: create OrderEntity\n(PENDING status)
    ORDER --> UI: 201 Created {orderId, totalPrice}
    UI --> USER: "Order created, proceed to payment"
end

== Step 4: Token Expiry and Refresh ==

USER -> UI: any authenticated request
UI -> PROP: Bearer <expired accessToken>
PROP -> PROP_FILTER: validate token
PROP_FILTER -> JWT_PROP: isTokenValid(token)
JWT_PROP -> JWT_PROP: check exp claim — EXPIRED
JWT_PROP --> PROP_FILTER: false
PROP_FILTER --> PROP: no authentication set
PROP --> UI: 401 Unauthorized

UI -> IAC: POST /api/v1/auth/refresh?refreshToken=<rt>
IAC -> IAC: validate refreshToken in DB\n(single-use, check expiry)
IAC -> IAC: revoke old refreshToken
IAC -> JWT_IAC: generateAccessToken() — new token
IAC --> UI: {new accessToken, new refreshToken}
UI -> PROP: retry with new Bearer token
PROP --> UI: 200 OK

note over IAC, UI
  Refresh tokens are single-use with rotation.
  POST /api/v1/auth/logout revokes ALL refresh tokens.
end note

@enduml
